bioghist.p:
Born 1932, Brooklyn, N.Y.; 1953 Pratt Institute (Advertising Design); 1953 L.W. Frohlich;
        1953-1955 military service, U.S. Army; 1955 Grey Advertising; 1956 Columbia Broadcasting;
        1957 Art Department, NTA Television Network; 1959 Art Director, Doyle Dane Bernbach; 1968,
        1970 voted "Number One Art Director in America" in national Ad Daily polls; 1969 Senior Vice
        President, DDB; 1970 partner, Harper Rosenfeld Sirowitz (renamed Rosenfeld Sirowitz &
        Lawson the same year, became Rosenfeld Sirowitz Humphrey & Strauss in 1986); 1982-1983
        President, One Club for Art and Copy; 1984 Honorary Doctorate of Fine Arts, Pratt Institute;
        1985 Art Directors Hall of Fame.

